  "title": "SITE SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>Inspecting construction sites regularly to identify and eliminate potential safety hazards.</p><ul><li>Supervising and instructing the construction team as well as subcontractors.</li><li>Educating site workers on construction safety regulations and accident protocol.</li><li>Enforcing site safety rules to minimize work-related accidents and injuries.</li><li>Handling site accidents in accordance with established accident protocol.</li><li>Maintaining an accurate record of construction employee attendance.</li><li>Evaluating the performance of construction employees and instituting disciplinary measures as needed.</li><li>Analyzing blueprints to ensure that construction projects meet design, safety, and budget specifications.</li><li>Recommending changes to construction operations or procedures to increase efficiency.</li></ul>",
